Preheat your oven to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450} lengthways into 1cm slices, then
chop into 1cm wide chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with
@salt{} and @pepper{} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{30-35%minutes}. Turn
halfway through.

Meanwhile, cut the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g} in half widthways. Keep one chunk of
cheese per person aside, then grate the rest.

In a large #bowl{}, add the @British beef mince{240%g}, season with the
@salt{1/4%tsp} for the burger and @pepper{}, then mix together with your hands.

Roll the mince into even-sized balls. Shape into 2cm thick burgers around a chunk
of cheese, ensuring they're well sealed (1 per person).

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

After the chips have cooked for ~{10%minutes}, pop the burgers onto a lightly oiled
baking tray and bake on the middle shelf of your oven until cooked through,
~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @British smoked bacon lardons{90%g} and stir-fry until golden,
~{4-5%minutes}. While the bacon fries, halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}.

Transfer the lardons to a bowl but keep the bacon fat in the pan.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook lardons
> thoroughly.

Pop the pan with the bacon fat back on medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{} if
it's a little dry.

When hot, add the onion and @sugar{1}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then fry
until soft and sweet, ~{8-10%minutes}. Remove from the heat.

Meanwhile, halve the @baby gem lettuce{1} lengthways through the root, then cut
each half lengthways into 3 wedges.

Mix together the @soured cream{75%g}, @water for the dressing{1.5} and
@cider vinegar{15%g} in a small bowl. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then set
the dressing aside.

When everything is nearly ready, place the grated cheese on top of the burgers
and bake until the cheese is melted, ~{3-4%minutes}. Halve the @glazed burger bun{2}
and pop onto a baking tray and into your oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once everything is ready, spread the @BBQ sauce{} over each bun base and top with
a burger.

> TIP: Scoop up any escaped cheese from the baking tray and pile on top.

Spoon on the caramelised @onion marmalade{20%g} and finish with the bun lid.

Share the baby gem wedges between your plates, cut-side up, and drizzle with the
creamy dressing. Top with the bacon and as much @crumbled blue cheese{30%g} as
you'd like. Serve the chips alongside. Enjoy!